<https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/submajor/1225-05> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/major/1225> ;
    skos:inScheme lmmha:scheme ;
    skos:narrower <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/1225-05-102>,
        <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/1225-05-103>,
        <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/1225-05-104>,
        <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/1225-05-800>,
        <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/1225-05-900> ;
    skos:notation "05" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Telecommunication Services 101 Licence Fee and Universal Access Levy services rendered. The following are some of the items covered by this minor head: - (i) Installation, reconnection and shifting fees. (ii) Charges for breakage, provision of additional facilities coloured sets etc. be opened: - (i) Royalties (ii) Miscellaneous items (Directories, Waste paper etc.) (i) Telegrams-domestic and (ii) Telegrams-International. (iii) Besides, suitable sub-heads may be opened for revenue realised on Deposit Account systems, Press messages etc. of services/Service fees recovered by the Telegraph Branch. The following are some of the items covered by this minor head: - (i) Charges for abbreviated telegraphic addresses (ii) Miscellaneous fees opened (i) Royalties (ii) Receipts from Guarantors; and (iii) Miscellaneous receipts (i) Advance Revenue (ii) Accounts Receivable. At the time of issue of bills, revenue will be directly booked to the relevant revenue head under ‘1225-Telecommunication Receipts’ viz., current year's revenue. Advance revenue and previous year's revenue (if the accounts of the previous year are open, otherwise it will be treated as current year's revenue) by per contra debit (minus credit) to the head '1225-Telecommunications Receipts-Telephones or Telegraphs Accounts Receivable’. Subsequent recoveries of the bills will be credited to the detailed head 'Accounts receivable'. not be operational for fresh transactions w.e.f. 01-04-2019."@en .

