<https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/submajor/3225-60> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/major/3225> ;
    skos:inScheme lmmha:scheme ;
    skos:narrower <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/3225-60-009>,
        <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/3225-60-101>,
        <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/3225-60-102>,
        <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/3225-60-190>,
        <https://data.commonerllp.org/ontology/lmmha/minor/3225-60-800> ;
    skos:notation "60" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Other Expenses include expenditure relating to General Manager (Projects) and their Administrative offices under distinct sub- heads. and Telephone Districts/Divisional Offices. (a) Establishment for Telephones (b) Establishment project Installations. Telecommunication Services. (i) Demand payable (ii) Unpaid wages (iii) Pre-paid expenses The liabilities accrued in a month but not discharged in the same month will be credited to 'Demands payable' by debit to the relevant minor head. The payment of such liabilities in the following month will be debited to ‘Demand payable'. Any credit balance relating to a month outstanding at the close of the following month will be transferred to 'Unpaid Wages' by debit to 'Demands Payable'. Pre-paid expenses will be directly debited to 'Pre-paid expenses' under the minor head 'Suspense' and will be transferred to the relevant-minor head in the accounts of the month to which they relate by credit (minus debit) to 'pre-paid expenses'. The sub heads of the nomenclature of the existing minor heads may be opened under the head 'Suspense' as and when necessary. termination of service etc. be operational for fresh transactions w.e.f. 01-04-2019."@en .

