    skos:notation "03" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Training recorded under a distinct sub head under the programme minor heads to which the terms of reference to the Committee/Commission are closely related. Expenditure relating to International Labour Conference and other General National Conference on Labour may be recorded as part of expenditure of the Ministry. Contribution to the International Labour Organisation will be recorded under the minor head ‘International Co-operation’. (See General direction No.3.2). wage boards. These may be shown under separate sub heads under this head. Expenditure on Labour Courts and Industrial Tribunals will also be recorded under this minor head. Inspectorate of Factories, Inspector of Steam Boilers, Labour Institutes, Rescue Services, Director-General of Mines Safety under distinct sub-heads. by minor heads for Coal, Mica and Iron Ore Mines labour welfare. All these minor heads may have sub heads’ Housing’, ‘Education’, ‘Health’ etc. as the case may be. measures for labour and industrial workers such as Family Pension-cum-Life Assurance scheme, Personal Injuries Compensation schemes etc. programme, National Institute of Labour etc. (i) National Commission on Rural Labour. (ii) Rural Workers cell. going abroad etc. accounted for under the major head ‘3475-General Economic Services’."@en .

