    skos:notation "4016" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Capital Outlay on Audit Capital Outlay on Currency, 4046 Coinage and Mint Deduct-depreciation (e) suspense and (f) Other expenditure. Plant and Machinery and (d) Other expenditure. relevant minor head, as per paragraph 4.3 of the General Directions. These minor heads have been retained temporarily till the balances (upto 1992-93) are segregated and transferred to the relevant minor heads. to the share holders of the RBI, consequent upon the nationalisation of the Banks, w.e.f 1.1.1949. of those imported, should be debited to the minor head ‘Nickel Coinage Account’ below the Major Head ‘8656-Coinage Account’ by contra credit (minus debit) to the Major Head ‘4046-Capital Outlay on Currency, Coinage and Mint’-Imports of Coins from Abroad-Deduct Receipts and Recoveries on Capital Outlay’. While the Debit to the Major Head’8656-Coinage Account’ will be for the face value of the coins, the minus debit to the Major Head ‘4046’ will be for the purchase price or for the proportionate purchase price in case the entire imported coins are not issued for circulation. The difference between the two should be taken as profit to be accounted for under the Mint Profit Account below the Major Head ‘8656-Coinage Account’. Capital Outlay on Other 4047 Fiscal Services (i) Land (ii) Buildings (iii) Plant and Machinery (iv)Other Expenditure and (v) Deduct-Depreciation. (i) Management (ii) Land (iii) Buildings (iv) Plant and Machinery (v) Suspense and (vi) Other Expenditure."@en .

